definitions.definition: The outermost -but-one whorl of a flower, composed of petals , when it is not the same in appearance as the outermost whorl (the calyx ); it usually comprises the petal , which may be fused.

main_definition: ( botany ) The outermost -but-one whorl of a flower, composed of petals , when it is not the same in appearance as the outermost whorl (the calyx ); it usually comprises the petal , which may be fused.
